
    Definition: A data worker uses spreadsheets daily to create valuable insights through presentations or reporting, often without having "data worker" as their job title.
    Common Tasks: Exporting data, building reports, using functions like logical functions (e.g., IF), and working with data from various sources such as IT or data warehouses.
    Skills to Develop: Proficiency in tools like Excel (Power Query, PivotTables), PowerPoint for visualizations, and documentation skills in Microsoft Word. Additionally, focus on effective presentation and communication skills.
